1
00:00:05,260 --> 00:00:08,739
(9 years ago, 2nd year of the Hongzheng)
(Big Flower, is your leg healed?)

2
00:00:08,740 --> 00:00:11,980
(I really want
to dance with you again.)

3
00:00:21,020 --> 00:00:23,180
Is this wood carving
the young emperor?

4
00:00:23,300 --> 00:00:24,179
Mm.

5
00:00:24,180 --> 00:00:26,540
Big Flower is my dearest friend.

6
00:00:26,780 --> 00:00:29,540
Being friends
with the Emperor is no blessing.

7
00:00:29,780 --> 00:00:31,099
Why not?

8
00:00:31,100 --> 00:00:32,339
Xiao Man,

9
00:00:32,340 --> 00:00:33,740
keep this in mind.

10
00:00:34,140 --> 00:00:35,820
It's because he bears a debt of guilt.

11
00:00:36,020 --> 00:00:37,779
He owes the Zhen family.

12
00:00:37,780 --> 00:00:40,540
Even across lifetimes,
he could never repay it clean.

13
00:00:41,140 --> 00:00:43,020
And between us and him,

14
00:00:43,380 --> 00:00:45,820
it will end only in death.

15
00:01:13,740 --> 00:01:16,220
Why does he bear such guilt?

16
00:01:17,087 --> 00:01:22,099
♪Do you know, our fingertips
are bound by one string♪

17
00:01:22,100 --> 00:01:26,699
♪Tied to an attachment
that blooms only to fade♪

18
00:01:26,700 --> 00:01:28,199
♪By your side once♪

19
00:01:28,200 --> 00:01:31,274
♪I laughed with the world
wild and free♪

20
00:01:31,275 --> 00:01:35,249
♪Yet now there's no one
to carry the story on♪

21
00:01:35,250 --> 00:01:40,170
♪Do you know you are the one string
woven through my fate♪

22
00:01:40,187 --> 00:01:44,899
♪Coiled through the years,
where longing sharpens into pain's line♪

23
00:01:44,900 --> 00:01:49,461
♪If love is meant to fall
more wretched the fiercer its flight♪

24
00:01:49,462 --> 00:01:54,645
♪Yet I still came to answer your call♪

25
00:01:54,925 --> 00:01:57,286
=Shall We Dance=

26
00:01:57,287 --> 00:02:00,057
=Episode 5=

27
00:02:01,980 --> 00:02:03,100
Your Majesty.

28
00:02:03,380 --> 00:02:04,899
There has been unrest lately.

29
00:02:04,900 --> 00:02:06,220
Strange incidents arise.

30
00:02:07,340 --> 00:02:08,219
However,

31
00:02:08,220 --> 00:02:10,180
there is one curious matter.

32
00:02:10,740 --> 00:02:12,660
Nearly everyone who harbours secrets

33
00:02:12,860 --> 00:02:14,940
seems to gather in one place.

34
00:02:14,980 --> 00:02:16,100
Where?

35
00:02:18,820 --> 00:02:21,140
Yanbo Parlor.

36
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:23,299
(Eastern Secret Chamber, Yanbo Parlor)

37
00:03:23,300 --> 00:03:24,620
Princess.

38
00:03:34,620 --> 00:03:36,140
Princess.

39
00:03:36,460 --> 00:03:39,379
(Chief of the Zhenzhe tribe, Yun Shuyan)
The envoy purchased black iron ore.

40
00:03:39,380 --> 00:03:40,859
I've looked into the bulk purchase.

41
00:03:40,860 --> 00:03:42,619
As expected,
they are forging black iron weapons

42
00:03:42,620 --> 00:03:44,339
in a highly concealed location,

43
00:03:44,340 --> 00:03:46,500
and continue to recruit
soldiers and allies.

44
00:03:48,380 --> 00:03:50,580
They've only just suffered a heavy blow,

45
00:03:51,300 --> 00:03:53,340
yet still have the funds for all this?

46
00:03:53,460 --> 00:03:55,140
Exactly my thought.

47
00:03:55,260 --> 00:03:57,299
So I kept digging.

48
00:03:57,300 --> 00:03:58,899
The silver they're using

49
00:03:58,900 --> 00:04:01,300
is clearly newly smelted.

50
00:04:01,780 --> 00:04:04,860
But one ingot appears
to have escaped the furnace,

51
00:04:04,940 --> 00:04:07,620
bearing the official
mint mark of Great Qian.

52
00:04:09,740 --> 00:04:13,100
I risked my life to track down
this intelligence for you, Princess.

53
00:04:13,140 --> 00:04:16,100
How do you intend to reward me?

54
00:04:22,540 --> 00:04:24,300
That can be arranged.

55
00:04:24,340 --> 00:04:26,619
I've acquired
some land along the frontier.

56
00:04:26,620 --> 00:04:28,779
There, waters run everywhere,

57
00:04:28,780 --> 00:04:29,979
and flowers bloom at every door.

58
00:04:29,980 --> 00:04:32,219
When I no longer
concern myself with palace affairs,

59
00:04:32,220 --> 00:04:34,700
I shall go there and build a few houses.

60
00:04:34,860 --> 00:04:36,739
Each day, I'll ride freely,

61
00:04:36,740 --> 00:04:38,500
living as my name suggests,

62
00:04:39,540 --> 00:04:42,460
enjoying years unbound and unrestrained.

63
00:04:43,300 --> 00:04:44,460
When that time comes,

64
00:04:47,500 --> 00:04:49,540
I'll take you in, you little rascal,

65
00:04:49,660 --> 00:04:51,739
and have you roam the world with me.

66
00:04:51,740 --> 00:04:53,140
We'll be free and unbridled.

67
00:04:53,180 --> 00:04:53,939
Truly?

68
00:04:53,940 --> 00:04:55,340
I give you my word.

69
00:04:57,380 --> 00:04:58,780
- Then it's settled.
- Then it's settled.

70
00:05:00,740 --> 00:05:02,219
(Western Secret Chamber)
Now, the Grand Princess appears

71
00:05:02,220 --> 00:05:04,139
(Yanbo Tower)
to have returned power to His Majesty,

72
00:05:04,140 --> 00:05:05,579
but she grows ever more ambitious.

73
00:05:05,580 --> 00:05:07,019
She rules from behind the curtain.

74
00:05:07,020 --> 00:05:08,579
And now she has grown close to

75
00:05:08,580 --> 00:05:10,580
Yun Shuyan of the Zhenzhe tribe.

76
00:05:10,740 --> 00:05:12,459
Whether it is military
authority of Great Qian

77
00:05:12,460 --> 00:05:14,619
or forces she can draw
upon beyond the borders,

78
00:05:14,620 --> 00:05:16,419
she holds both firmly in hand.

79
00:05:16,420 --> 00:05:18,580
Does she mean
to become another Wu Zetian?

80
00:05:19,260 --> 00:05:21,380
She may not harbour Wu Zhao's ambitions,

81
00:05:21,580 --> 00:05:23,099
but power is a thing

82
00:05:23,100 --> 00:05:25,299
that once grasped

83
00:05:25,300 --> 00:05:27,300
can never easily be relinquished.

84
00:05:28,620 --> 00:05:30,580
It can even drive one to madness.

85
00:05:32,740 --> 00:05:35,780
That young emperor has
played the fool for ten years.

86
00:05:36,060 --> 00:05:37,300
By now,

87
00:05:37,620 --> 00:05:39,580
he must have had enough of his aunt.

88
00:05:39,700 --> 00:05:41,059
You mean to say...

89
00:05:41,060 --> 00:05:42,499
Aside from the Zhenzhe tribe,

90
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:45,660
other border tribes
are growing stronger as well?

91
00:05:46,020 --> 00:05:48,740
Now you command
the Ministry of War at court,

92
00:05:48,860 --> 00:05:51,580
while I manoeuvre within the palace.

93
00:05:51,940 --> 00:05:53,060
In addition,

94
00:05:53,260 --> 00:05:55,899
I have secured allies
at the frontier to correspond with us.

95
00:05:55,900 --> 00:05:57,620
When the moment is ripe,

96
00:05:58,100 --> 00:06:00,060
the great undertaking will succeed.

97
00:06:02,180 --> 00:06:03,460
I've learned that

98
00:06:04,900 --> 00:06:06,139
the Grand Princess

99
00:06:06,140 --> 00:06:08,980
and Yun Shuyan,
leader of the Zhenzhe tribe,

100
00:06:09,620 --> 00:06:11,260
Jia Yi of the Directorate of Ceremonial,

101
00:06:11,460 --> 00:06:13,700
and Minister of War Sun Gong,

102
00:06:13,900 --> 00:06:16,420
have each held secret talks
in the chambers of Yanbo Parlor.

103
00:06:17,820 --> 00:06:19,300
I never would have thought

104
00:06:19,860 --> 00:06:21,099
that Yanbo Parlor would become

105
00:06:21,100 --> 00:06:23,740
the most
sought-after place in the capital.

106
00:06:24,580 --> 00:06:26,700
Who else visited the place?

107
00:06:28,260 --> 00:06:29,380
There is one more.

108
00:06:31,260 --> 00:06:32,380
Xiao Man.

109
00:06:47,220 --> 00:06:48,340
Wait.

110
00:06:49,780 --> 00:06:51,260
Sun Gong...

111
00:06:51,900 --> 00:06:53,500
Is he not my aunt's man?

112
00:06:55,220 --> 00:06:57,740
Then what ties
does Jia Yi have with them?

113
00:06:59,820 --> 00:07:01,060
And Xiao Man...

114
00:07:02,620 --> 00:07:04,260
Who exactly is he?

115
00:07:05,740 --> 00:07:07,100
Friend or foe?

116
00:07:09,980 --> 00:07:12,860
Ten years between
life and death, all lost to the void.

117
00:07:13,300 --> 00:07:14,939
Though the view remains,
people have changed.

118
00:07:14,940 --> 00:07:17,580
Everything has come to nothing.

119
00:07:20,540 --> 00:07:22,300
Those who still carry hope

120
00:07:24,140 --> 00:07:25,780
must not disappoint me.

121
00:07:33,580 --> 00:07:35,459
Why has Your Majesty brought me here?

122
00:07:35,460 --> 00:07:36,900
To meet an old acquaintance.

123
00:07:45,100 --> 00:07:46,219
Ever since my return,

124
00:07:46,220 --> 00:07:47,979
Your Majesty keeps staring at me.

125
00:07:47,980 --> 00:07:49,540
What are you looking at?

126
00:07:50,100 --> 00:07:51,500
Because you've changed.

127
00:07:53,260 --> 00:07:54,540
How so?

128
00:07:56,900 --> 00:07:58,019
You've grown taller.

129
00:07:58,020 --> 00:07:59,260
More handsome.

130
00:08:00,340 --> 00:08:01,980
No longer like when you were little,

131
00:08:02,020 --> 00:08:03,500
all flustered and adorable.

132
00:08:04,860 --> 00:08:06,019
Flustered and adorable?

133
00:08:06,020 --> 00:08:07,060
That's right.

134
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:09,219
If this were back in our childhood,

135
00:08:09,220 --> 00:08:10,620
you'd definitely be...

136
00:08:11,180 --> 00:08:12,779
"Ah, Your Majesty,

137
00:08:12,780 --> 00:08:14,380
I know my fault.

138
00:08:14,420 --> 00:08:16,220
I will never repeat the same mistake."

139
00:08:18,180 --> 00:08:19,299
Good.

140
00:08:19,300 --> 00:08:20,499
Exactly like that.

141
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:22,100
Your Majesty is impressive.

142
00:08:22,620 --> 00:08:23,700
Xiao Man,

143
00:08:24,100 --> 00:08:25,820
I always try to find

144
00:08:26,220 --> 00:08:28,100
the look you had as a child.

145
00:08:33,140 --> 00:08:34,940
Why not act it out now?

146
00:08:40,100 --> 00:08:41,539
I command you,

147
00:08:41,540 --> 00:08:43,060
do it at once.

148
00:08:44,380 --> 00:08:45,500
No.

149
00:08:47,260 --> 00:08:49,020
Go on, just do one.

150
00:08:49,260 --> 00:08:51,140
Do it for your dearest friend.

151
00:08:57,860 --> 00:09:00,020
Ah, Your Majesty.

152
00:09:02,380 --> 00:09:03,540
That's it.

153
00:09:04,020 --> 00:09:05,140
Another one.

154
00:09:05,620 --> 00:09:07,340
Ah, Your Majesty.

155
00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:08,219
I...

156
00:09:08,220 --> 00:09:09,140
I am...

157
00:09:14,380 --> 00:09:15,500
I can't do it.

158
00:09:15,820 --> 00:09:16,780
I can never undo that.

159
00:09:17,620 --> 00:09:19,099
You couldn't call yourself a servant,

160
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:19,860
right?

161
00:09:22,580 --> 00:09:23,740
I knew it.

162
00:09:23,980 --> 00:09:25,299
Ever since you returned,

163
00:09:25,300 --> 00:09:27,219
you've been
avoiding that form of address.

164
00:09:27,220 --> 00:09:29,420
You're avoiding
your identity as a eunuch.

165
00:09:33,380 --> 00:09:34,300
Very well.

166
00:09:35,140 --> 00:09:37,579
Today, I grant you
pardon on two matters.

167
00:09:37,580 --> 00:09:38,540
First,

168
00:09:38,580 --> 00:09:40,300
stop referring to yourself as a servant.

169
00:09:40,460 --> 00:09:41,340
Second,

170
00:09:41,580 --> 00:09:43,220
when there is no one else,

171
00:09:44,460 --> 00:09:45,820
call me by my name.

172
00:09:48,820 --> 00:09:50,020
Like now.

173
00:09:51,380 --> 00:09:52,700
Your Majesty.

174
00:09:52,780 --> 00:09:54,620
What was the name again?

175
00:09:55,260 --> 00:09:56,380
Big Flower?

176
00:09:56,420 --> 00:09:57,580
No.

177
00:10:01,420 --> 00:10:02,579
I am Chu Ying,

178
00:10:02,580 --> 00:10:03,740
nineteen years of age.

179
00:10:03,940 --> 00:10:06,180
May I ask this young gentleman's name,

180
00:10:06,660 --> 00:10:08,380
and how many years he has seen?

181
00:10:14,220 --> 00:10:17,020
I am but one year older,
Young Master Chu.

182
00:10:17,140 --> 00:10:18,260
My name is...

183
00:10:27,540 --> 00:10:28,900
My name is Xiao Man.

184
00:10:32,660 --> 00:10:34,220
Why do you always avoid me?

185
00:10:35,100 --> 00:10:37,020
Is there something wrong with that name?

186
00:10:37,340 --> 00:10:38,460
No.

187
00:10:39,220 --> 00:10:40,340
Good.

188
00:10:40,540 --> 00:10:41,779
Then listen closely.

189
00:10:41,780 --> 00:10:43,139
To me, "Xiao Man"

190
00:10:43,140 --> 00:10:45,420
is the most
beautiful name in this world.

191
00:10:46,340 --> 00:10:48,780
He gave me warmth
when I was most helpless.

192
00:10:49,100 --> 00:10:50,619
He embodies a friendship

193
00:10:50,620 --> 00:10:52,420
I have carried for ten years.

194
00:10:53,060 --> 00:10:55,180
I will not allow anyone to erase him.

195
00:10:59,460 --> 00:11:01,940
I thought we were here
to meet an old acquaintance?

196
00:11:05,140 --> 00:11:05,900
Come on.

197
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:08,980
Look who's here.

198
00:11:11,940 --> 00:11:12,419
This is

199
00:11:12,420 --> 00:11:13,540
Little Flower.

200
00:11:15,780 --> 00:11:16,980
You've been

201
00:11:17,220 --> 00:11:19,059
looking after Little Flower
after I left?

202
00:11:19,060 --> 00:11:20,180
I have.

203
00:11:20,500 --> 00:11:22,219
You were gone a full ten years.

204
00:11:22,220 --> 00:11:24,460
Little Flower's grown
into Old Flower now.

205
00:11:24,860 --> 00:11:26,420
Even its fur has faded.

206
00:11:26,940 --> 00:11:28,660
Lucky you still got to see it.

207
00:11:29,940 --> 00:11:31,100
Take it away.

208
00:11:37,940 --> 00:11:39,100
Thank you.

209
00:11:49,020 --> 00:11:50,580
After you left,

210
00:11:50,860 --> 00:11:53,060
I kept everything you left behind.

211
00:11:53,580 --> 00:11:54,739
Ten years you were gone,

212
00:11:54,740 --> 00:11:55,940
without a single word.

213
00:11:56,620 --> 00:11:58,419
The only way I could ease my thoughts

214
00:11:58,420 --> 00:11:59,179
was to look

215
00:11:59,180 --> 00:12:01,340
at the things you left me.

216
00:12:02,700 --> 00:12:04,940
In my hardest, most helpless moments,

217
00:12:06,220 --> 00:12:08,180
I could only confide in Little Flower.

218
00:12:10,820 --> 00:12:12,740
Perhaps you're not one for sentiment.

219
00:12:13,260 --> 00:12:14,940
After all, beyond these palace walls,

220
00:12:15,180 --> 00:12:16,900
there are so many new faces,

221
00:12:16,940 --> 00:12:18,260
so many new things.

222
00:12:20,580 --> 00:12:21,820
I remember.

223
00:12:21,940 --> 00:12:23,540
I remember everything.

224
00:12:24,500 --> 00:12:26,419
It was those memories

225
00:12:26,420 --> 00:12:28,580
that carried me through my darkest days.

226
00:12:28,700 --> 00:12:29,820
Darkest days?

227
00:12:31,580 --> 00:12:34,020
This is where you and I first met.

228
00:12:34,860 --> 00:12:36,900
I came every night to bring you food.

229
00:12:37,460 --> 00:12:38,939
One bitterly cold evening,

230
00:12:38,940 --> 00:12:40,540
your nose was running from the chill.

231
00:12:40,740 --> 00:12:41,860
So then...

232
00:12:48,260 --> 00:12:50,060
That was how it began for us, wasn't it?

233
00:12:50,700 --> 00:12:51,659
It was.

234
00:12:51,660 --> 00:12:52,780
Just like that.

235
00:12:53,380 --> 00:12:54,420
Xiao Man,

236
00:12:54,620 --> 00:12:56,499
from now on,
let us be as we once were.

237
00:12:56,500 --> 00:12:57,780
No distance between us.

238
00:12:57,820 --> 00:12:58,980
Will you?

239
00:13:02,980 --> 00:13:05,780
"I would buy
cassia blossoms and sail with wine,

240
00:13:05,980 --> 00:13:07,300
yet in the end,

241
00:13:07,740 --> 00:13:09,060
it is not our wanderings."

242
00:13:21,340 --> 00:13:22,740
Listen to this melody.

243
00:13:23,260 --> 00:13:24,179
After you left,

244
00:13:24,180 --> 00:13:26,780
I had the musicians of the Imperial
Music Office play it for ten years.

245
00:13:27,380 --> 00:13:29,580
But no one ever danced it with me again.

246
00:13:31,700 --> 00:13:33,220
Do you still remember the steps?

247
00:13:34,700 --> 00:13:35,820
I remember.

248
00:13:38,180 --> 00:13:39,180
Well...

249
00:14:02,362 --> 00:14:06,282
♪I wanted to ask you
the meaning of forever♪

250
00:14:06,687 --> 00:14:09,807
♪Is it longing that never rests♪

251
00:14:10,462 --> 00:14:13,719
♪Love that echoes without end♪

252
00:14:15,012 --> 00:14:18,607
♪Or promises that can't be kept♪

253
00:14:18,980 --> 00:14:20,100
Xiao Man.

254
00:14:21,580 --> 00:14:23,180
I have never changed.

255
00:14:24,180 --> 00:14:25,540
As long as you are the same,

256
00:14:26,460 --> 00:14:28,220
we can go back to
how it was back then.

257
00:14:29,762 --> 00:14:32,569
♪How cruel♪

258
00:14:32,687 --> 00:14:36,844
♪Love blooms and withers♪

259
00:14:39,037 --> 00:14:43,119
♪The more I try to forget
the fiercer the love burns♪

260
00:14:43,412 --> 00:14:47,507
♪The more I retreat
the sharper it feels♪

261
00:14:47,874 --> 00:14:51,186
♪How am I supposed to let go♪

262
00:14:51,187 --> 00:14:55,269
♪And bring this story to an end♪

263
00:14:57,037 --> 00:15:00,644
♪After ten thousand years
adrift in the mortal world♪

264
00:15:01,037 --> 00:15:05,182
♪Why is my wish still unfulfilled♪

265
00:15:05,249 --> 00:15:13,911
♪How absurd
that this longing just won't die♪

266
00:15:13,912 --> 00:15:18,924
♪Do you know, our fingertips
are bound by one string♪

267
00:15:18,925 --> 00:15:23,524
♪Tied to an attachment
that blooms only to fade♪

268
00:15:23,525 --> 00:15:25,024
♪By your side once♪

269
00:15:25,025 --> 00:15:28,099
♪I laughed with the world
wild and free♪

270
00:15:28,100 --> 00:15:31,420
♪Yet now there's no one
to carry the story on♪
